<h2>Attribute vs Element</h2>
<p>HTML has both a <code>cite</code> attribute and a <code>&lt;cite&gt;</code> element. They are related but different.</p>

<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Feature</th><th><code>cite</code> Attribute</th><th><code>&lt;cite&gt;</code> Element</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td>What it holds</td><td>A URL</td><td>The title of a work</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Visible</td><td>No</td><td>Yes (rendered in italics by default)</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Used on</td><td><code>&lt;blockquote&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;del&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;ins&gt;</code></td><td>Inline, anywhere</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Purpose</td><td>Machine-readable source link</td><td>Human-readable work title</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

